Windows 11 Documentation - OS_Wiki

System Name: Windows 11
Kernel: Windows NT (NT 10.0)
Based on: Windows NT family
Created by: Microsoft
Maintained by: Microsoft
Initial release: October 5, 2021
Source model: Closed source (proprietary)
License: Microsoft Commercial Software License
Architecture support: x86_64 (64-bit) only; no official 32-bit edition
Package manager: Microsoft Store / Winget (Windows Package Manager)
Desktop Environment: Windows Shell (Fluent Design)
System type: Desktop / Workstation
Target audience: General users, home users, enterprise environments, gamers, and creators.
Not recommended for: Very old hardware, devices without TPM 2.0, or users who prefer fully open-source systems.
Official site: https://www.microsoft.com/windows
ISO size for download: ~5 GB (varies by edition and release)
Description: Windows 11 is a proprietary operating system developed by Microsoft as the successor to Windows 10. It features a redesigned interface using the Fluent Design language, a centered taskbar, and improved window management through Snap Layouts and Snap Groups. Windows 11 requires modern hardware, including TPM 2.0 and Secure Boot. It includes the Microsoft Store and supports the Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL) and Android app compatibility through the Amazon Appstore on supported builds.
